com.opengamma.strata.market.value

Class ForwardPriceIndexValues

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.opengamma.strata.market.value.ForwardPriceIndexValues
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MarketDataValue<PriceIndexValues>, PriceIndexValues, Serializable, Bean, ImmutableBean

    public final class ForwardPriceIndexValues
extends Object
implements PriceIndexValues, ImmutableBean, Serializable
    Provides values for a Price index from a forward curve.

    This provides historic and forward rates for a single PriceIndex, such as 'US-CPI-U'.

    This implementation is based on an underlying forward curve.

    • Method Detail

      • of

        public static ForwardPriceIndexValues of(PriceIndex index,
                                         LocalDate valuationDate,
                                         LocalDateDoubleTimeSeries fixings,
                                         InterpolatedNodalCurve curve)
        Creates a new ForwardPriceIndexValues with no seasonality adjustment.

        The curve is specified by an instance of InterpolatedNodalCurve. Each x-value on the curve is the number of months between the valuation month and the estimation month. For example, zero represents the valuation month, one the next month and so on.

        The time-series contains one value per month and must have at least one entry. The value is stored in the time-series on the last date of each month (which may be a non-working day).

        The curve will be altered to be consistent with the time-series. The last element of the series is added as the first point of the interpolated curve to ensure a coherent transition.

        Parameters:
        index - the Price index
        valuationDate - the valuation date for which the curve is valid
        fixings - the known historical fixings
        curve - the underlying forward curve for index estimation
        Returns:
        the values instance

      • of

        public static ForwardPriceIndexValues of(PriceIndex index,
                                         LocalDate valuationDate,
                                         LocalDateDoubleTimeSeries fixings,
                                         InterpolatedNodalCurve curve,
                                         DoubleArray seasonality)
        Creates a new ForwardPriceIndexValues with seasonality adjustment.

        The curve is specified by an instance of InterpolatedNodalCurve. Each x-value on the curve is the number of months between the valuation month and the estimation month. For example, zero represents the valuation month, one the next month and so on.

        The time-series contains one value per month and must have at least one entry. The value is stored in the time-series on the last date of each month (which may be a non-working day).

        The curve will be altered to be consistent with the time-series. The last element of the series is added as the first point of the interpolated curve to ensure a coherent transition.

        Parameters:
        index - the Price index
        valuationDate - the valuation date for which the curve is valid
        fixings - the known historical fixings
        curve - the underlying forward curve for index estimation
        seasonality - the seasonality adjustment, size 12, index zero is January, where the value 1 means no seasonality adjustment
        Returns:
        the values instance

      • value

        public double value(YearMonth month)
        Description copied from interface: PriceIndexValues
        Gets the historic or forward rate at the specified fixing month.

        The rate of the Price index, such as 'US-CPI-U', varies over time. This method obtains the actual or estimated rate for the month.

        This retrieves the actual rate if the fixing month is before the valuation month, or the estimated rate if the fixing month is after the valuation month. If the month equals the valuation month, then the best available value is returned.

        Specified by:
        value in interface PriceIndexValues
        Parameters:
        month - the fixing month to query the rate for
        Returns:
        the value of the index, either historic or forward

      • valuePointSensitivity

        public PointSensitivityBuilder valuePointSensitivity(YearMonth fixingMonth)
        Description copied from interface: PriceIndexValues
        Calculates the point sensitivity of the historic or forward value at the specified fixing month.

        This returns a sensitivity instance referring to the curve used to determine the forward value. If a time-series was used, then there is no sensitivity. The sensitivity refers to the result of PriceIndexValues.value(YearMonth).

        Specified by:
        valuePointSensitivity in interface PriceIndexValues
        Parameters:
        fixingMonth - the month to find the sensitivity for
        Returns:
        the point sensitivity of the value

      • getSeasonality

        public DoubleArray getSeasonality()
        Gets describes the seasonal adjustments. The array has a dimension of 12, one element for each month, starting from January. The adjustments are multiplicative. For each month, the price index is the one obtained from the interpolated part of the curve multiplied by the seasonal adjustment.
        Returns:
        the value of the property, not null
